headline: 1 Wall Street Analyst Thinks Palantir Stock Is Going to $60. Is It a Sell?
summary: Following Palantir Technologies' (NASDAQ: PLTR) recent customer event, Jefferies analyst Brent Hill maintained an underperform (sell) rating on the shares with a $60 price target, implying potential downside of 29% from the current share price.  Palantir stock has had an incredible run over the past two years, climbing 971%.  The company's artificial intelligence (AI) platform has been in strong demand, but more analysts on Wall Street are starting to sound the alarm on the stock's high valuation.

headline: Should You Forget Palantir and Buy These 2 Millionaire-Maker Stocks Instead?
summary: Palantir Technologies (NASDAQ: PLTR) has been one of the hottest stocks on the market in the past couple of years, rising an incredible 1,000% as of this writing and beating the S&P 500 index's gains of just 45% during this period by a heavy margin.  The software specialist's stunning rally can be attributed to the terrific demand for its Artificial Intelligence Platform (AIP), which enables customers to embed generative AI capabilities into their operations.  The demand for Palantir's AIP has been so strong that the company's growth accelerated impressively in 2024.
